'''''Black Workers' Struggle for Equality in Birmingham''''' is a 2001 [[book]] written by [[David Montgomery (historian)|David Montgomery]], Professor of History [[Emeritus]] at [[Yale University]], in collaboration with [[Horace Huntley]] of the [[Birmingham Civil Rights Institute]]. The book makes use of oral histories to explain the interactions between [[African-American]] workers and [[labor unions]] in the post-[[American Civil War|Civil War]] [[American South]].

