{{Infobox person | name = Christian von Ditfurth <!-- include middle initial, if not specified in birth_name --> | image = Christian von ditfurth.jpg <!-- filename only, no "File:" or "Image:" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software --> | caption = Christian von Ditfurth | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name --> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1953|3|14|mf=y}} | birth_place = [[Würzburg]], [[Lower Franconia]] | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = [[Germany|German]] | other_names = | occupation = Author | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = }}
'''Wolf-Christian von Ditfurth''' (born March 14, 1953) is a [[Germany|German]] author and historian.<ref>[http://d-nb.info/gnd/11568641X German Biography Database]</ref> He was a member of the [[German Communist Party]]<ref>{{cite web|author=Foster, Anne|url=http://www.europolar.eu/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=41&Itemid=30&lang=en|title=Crime Fiction as Historical Documentation|publisher=Europolar.eu|accessdate=July 25, 2009}}</ref> from 1973 to 1983. In January 1998, he joined the [[Social Democratic Party of Germany|SPD]], remaining a member for two years.<ref name=CDlautVL>{{cite web|url=https://www.welt.de/print-welt/article546557/Die-sind-ja-gar-nicht-mehr-links.html|title= Die sind ja gar nicht mehr links!|author=Vera Lengsfeld |date= 11 November 2000 |work=Christian von Ditfurth rechnet mit der SPD ab|publisher=WeltN24 GmbH, Berlin|accessdate=13 July 2017}}</ref> During the twenty-first century he has not joined a political party.
As a journalist, Ditfurth has published numerous articles in ''[[Der Spiegel]]''. Since 1999 also been a writer of sensational and detective novels.
A member of the Ditfurth family, his father [[Hoimar von Ditfurth]] was a journalist, doctor, popular television presenter and writer, while his sister, [[Jutta Ditfurth]], is a journalist and politician.
