{{Infobox museum | name = City Museum of Mitrovica | image = The City Museum of Mitrovica.jpg | caption =The City Museum of Mitrovica | established = 1952 | collection = | area = | location = [[Mitrovica, Kosovo|Mitrovica]], [[Kosovo]] | visitors = | publictransit = |director = Hajrullah Mustafa <ref name="KM"> [https://kk.rks-gov.net/mitrovice/News/Lajmet/Shenohet-60-vjetori-i--punes-se-Muzeut-te-qytetit-.aspx Komuna e Mitrovicës], in Albanian.</ref> | website = }}
The '''City Museum of Mitrovica''' ({{lang-sq|Muzeu i qytetit të Mitrovicës}}) is a museum in [[Mitrovica, Kosovo|Mitrovica]], [[Kosovo]], established in 1952. It is currently housed in the former [[Yugoslav army|Yugoslav Army]] House located in the city center. <ref name="KM"/>
The museum holds over 1,000 archaeological artifacts from different historical periods, dating back to the [[Illyria]]n civilization, and displays over 800 [[ethnological]] handiworks, representing the local diversity. The museum houses historical materials and documents and [[geological]] and [[numismatic]] collections among others. <ref name="KM"/> <ref name="Kultplus"> [http://www.kultplus.com/?id=7&l=1905 Illyrian relics in the City Museum of Mitrovics], in Albanian.</ref>
The City Museum of Mitrovica organizes various of events and activities, including [[Mitro të dua]] ({{lang-en|Mitro[vica], i love you}}), an annual event focused on the presentation and the digitization of cultural treasures of Mitrovica, with particular emphasis on the [[performing arts]], initiating this way the foundation of [[contemporary art]] section within the museum. <ref name="heyevent"> [http://heyevent.com/venue/g3ud25akdzkpea City Museum of Mitrovica's events]</ref> <ref name="Mitro të dua"> [http://www.gazetaexpress.com/arte/muzeu-i-mitrovices-hap-edicionin-e-dyte-te-mitro-te-dua-201808/ City Museum of Mitrovica's organizes the second edition of 'Mitro të dua'] in Albanian.</ref>
