'''Michael Borgolte''' (born 1948) is a German Historian. Besides the history of medieval [[Financial endowment|endowments]] he studies mainly the [[Comparative history]] of Europe and the [[World history|Global history]] of the Middle Ages.

== Career ==
Borgolte was educated at the [[University of Münster]], where he gained his doctorate in 1975. In 1981 he qualified as a professor at the [[University of Freiburg]], where he was assistant to the [[Palaeography|palaeographer]] Johanne Authenrieth from 1975 onwards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.geschichte.hu-berlin.de/de/bereiche-und-lehrstuehle/migei/personen/borgolte|title=Prof. Dr. phil. Michael  Borgolte — Mittelalterliche Geschichte I|first=Marlon|last=Maschkiwitz|website=www.geschichte.hu-berlin.de}}</ref> in 1991 he was one of the first professors newly appointed to [[Humboldt University of Berlin|Humboldt-University]] after the [[Berlin Wall]] came down. He held the chair for Medieval History until 2018. Since 2007 Borgolte is a member of the [[Berlin-Brandenburg Academy of Sciences and Humanities|Berlin-Brandenburgische Akademie der Wissenschaften]] and as such delegated to the scientific board of the [[Monumenta Germaniae Historica]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mgh.de/mgh/zentraldirektion/?sword_list[0]=borgolte|title=Members of the MGH Zentraldirektion|website=www.mgh.de}}</ref> Together with [[Bernd Schneidmüller]] he was coordinator of the research program [http://www.spp1173.uni-hd.de/ SPP 1173] "Integration und Desintegration der Kulturen im europäischen Mittelalter", funded by the [[Deutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft|German Research Foundation]]. In 2011 he was awarded with an [[European Research Council|ERC]] Advanced Grant for his research program "Foundations in Medieval Societies — Crosscultural Comparisons".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hu-berlin.de/de/pr/nachrichten/archiv/nr1111/pm_111121_00|title=ERC Advanced Grant 2011 für Prof. Dr. Michael Borgolte — Presseportal|first=Hans-Christoph|last=Keller|website=www.hu-berlin.de}}</ref> Collaborating with the [[Byzantine studies|Byzantinist]] [[Zachary Chitwood]], the [[Indology|Indologist]] [[Annette Schmiedchen]], the medieval historian [[Tillmann Lohse]] and others he prepared a three volume encyclopedia on this topic which promptly stimulated scholarly discussions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hsozkult.de/publicationreview/id/rezbuecher-25586|title=Rezension zu: Enzyklopädie des Stiftungswesens|first=Hugener,|last=Rainer|website=H-Soz-Kult. Kommunikation und Fachinformation für die Geschichtswissenschaften}}</ref>

== Further reading ==
Scheller, Benjamin (2014), "Philosophischer Kopf und wissenschaftlicher Unternehmer: Eine Charakteristik Michael Borgoltes anstelle einer Einführung", In: Ed. Tillmann Lohse et al. ''Europa in der Welt des Mittelalters: Ein Colloquium für und mit Michael Borgolte.'' Berlin; New York, p.&nbsp;1–9 {{ISBN|978-3-11-035096-8}}

