'''Monica Pellecer Alecio''' is a [[Guatemala]]n archaeologist who in 2005 led a team that found the oldest known [[Maya civilization|Maya]] royal tomb to date, belonging to an early Maya king (150BC). It was uncovered beneath a small [[pyramid]] at [[San Bartolo (Maya site)|San Bartolo]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/10452176/ns/technology_and_science-science/ | title=Oldest Maya Mural Wows Archaeologists | publisher=MSNBC Science | date=15 December 2005 | accessdate=April 17, 2011}}</ref>

